## The $739 Problem

*— Denken, Founder*
"The most expensive social media management tool in the world costs $739 a month. Ours costs forty-two cents. Same platforms. More features. Because the money goes to YOU, not shareholders."

### What You're Paying For (Elsewhere)

You have a TikTok. And an Instagram. And a Twitter. And a LinkedIn. Maybe a YouTube, a Facebook page, a Threads, a Bluesky.

You make something — a video, a post, an announcement. And then you do the dance: copy text, open TikTok, paste, adjust, post. Open Instagram, paste, adjust, post. Open Twitter, paste, truncate because 280 characters, post. Open LinkedIn, paste, add professional tone, post.

Every. Single. Time.

That's not a workflow. That's a tax on your time.

> **The Social Media Tax**
>
If you post to 5 platforms and each one takes 5 minutes to adapt and post, that's 25 minutes per post. Post three times a week? That's 75 minutes. Per week. Over 60 hours a year — just copying and pasting the same content into different boxes.

The industry's solution: pay someone else to do it. The cost: $15 to $739 per month.

