# Why Start a Guild?

> "Six paths. Six levels. All lead to Captain."

A Guild is your professional crew on Liana Banyan. Makers, designers, farmers, drivers, tutors, developers — whatever you do, a Guild is where you do it together.

Here's what you get.

---

## 1. Your Own Banner

Your guild's first act is a design contest. Pool Credits into the treasury, open submissions, vote as a guild. The winner's design becomes your Guild Banner — displayed on your guild page, your members' profiles, and the guild directory.

Not just a banner. Your guild can contest a full visual identity: theme, mascot, icon, color palette. Each one created by your members, chosen by your members.

**Your guild's look is YOUR vote.**

---

## 2. Your Own Treasury

Every guild has a Collective Treasury — a pooled Credit account funded by voluntary member contributions.

Small purchases (below your guild's threshold): your Guild Leader approves. Large purchases: the guild votes. Emergency reserve (10%): requires a supermajority.

Every Credit in, every Credit out — visible to every member on your guild's ledger.

What can the treasury fund?
- Design contests (banners, themes, mascots)
- Group purchases (bulk materials, shared tools)
- Bounties (Larks with Credit rewards for improvements)
- Events (workshops, showcases, meetups)
- Member support (LB Card funding for a member in need)

---

## 3. Your Own Theme

Your guild can have its own visual presentation of the entire platform. Same features, same content — different look. Your guild votes on which theme represents you.

When a guild member logs in, they see the platform through the guild's theme. It's not cosmetic — it's identity.

And if enough guilds create enough themes, the whole platform becomes a living design experiment. Community-governed visual identity. CSS Zen Garden, but democratic.

---

## 4. Your Own Economy

Guilds aren't just social — they're economic.

- **Crew Tables**: Form work crews with guild members for projects
- **Volume Discounts**: Aggregate purchasing power for better prices
- **Guild Side Quests**: A guild-specific job board
- **Design Contests**: Earn Credits and Marks by winning
