# Find a Bug, Earn a Coin
## How the X-Ray Bounty Arena Turns Quality into a Game

*Cephas — Liana Banyan Knowledge Base*

---

Have you ever noticed something wrong on a website — a misaligned button, a typo, a page that looks broken on your phone — and thought, "Someone should fix that"?

What if that someone was you? And what if you got paid for it?

### X-Ray Goggles: See Everything

The X-Ray Bounty Arena starts with a simple tool: X-Ray Goggles. Toggle them on, and every element on the page becomes inspectable. Hover over a button, a headline, an image — you can see what it is and whether something's off.

When you spot an error, click it. A gold coin flips on screen. You just earned your first Mark.

That's it. One click. One coin. One contribution.

### Three Ways to Earn

Not everyone finds errors the same way. The Arena has three tiers:

**Scout** — You find the problem. One click, fast. You don't need to explain it or know how to fix it. Just click and move on. The system captures a screenshot automatically.

**Scribe** — You describe the problem. What's wrong, what it should look like, what device you're on. You can document errors other Scouts found — you don't have to find them yourself. Some people are better at explaining than hunting. That's valuable too.

**Fixer** — You propose the actual solution. New CSS, corrected text, a layout change. This earns the most Marks because it takes the most skill. But anyone can try.

A single error can pay three different people. The Scout who clicked, the Scribe who documented, and the Fixer who solved it. Teamwork, rewarded individually.

### The Daily Tracker

When X-Ray mode is active, a small counter floats in the corner of your screen:

> 12M today | 5 days

That's your daily Marks earned and your streak — consecutive days of participation. Streaks earn bonus Marks. The counter is collapsible (it won't get in your way) but always there when you want it.

And yes — there's an optional coin sound. Toggle it on in settings if you want the full arcade experience. Off by default, because not everyone wants their Tuesday morning to sound like a Mario level.

### Bounties: Make Your Own

See something that needs fixing but nobody's posted it yet? Create a bounty. Stake your own Marks as a reward. Other members can add to the pool, making the bounty more attractive. When someone proposes a fix, you approve it — or the community votes.

You can even fulfill your own bounty. Found the problem AND know the fix? Do both. Earn both.

### The Auction

Every 24 hours, all proposed design changes go into the Design Auction. Each one displays for 10 seconds. Members bid Marks on the ones they want to see go live. The winner becomes the new design — displayed to everyone until the next auction replaces it.

Don't like the winning design? You can keep the classic look in your personal settings. Your platform, your choice.

### Why It Matters

Most platforms fix bugs when engineers get around to it. The Bounty Arena puts quality in the hands of every member. The people using the platform are the people improving it — and earning Marks for doing so.

Your grandmother can be a Scout. Your neighbor's kid can be a Fixer. The platform gets better. Everyone earns.

